main event: On 9 October 1963, multiple witnesses in Sioux City, Iowa observed a bright circular object described as luminous and erratic in movement.
interesting points: The object was reported to move rapidly and change directions abruptly.,Witnesses included civilians and police officers.,The sighting lasted for approximately 15 minutes.,The object appeared to be at a height of 1,000 to 2,000 feet.,Authorities were notified, but no photographs were taken.
witness description: Witnesses included civilians and police officers in the area.
